	     <form action=http://eqdb.allakhazam.com/strategy/mrate.pl name=f101197043325464>
	     <tr><td id=headerrow colspan=2 class=mform valign=top><a name=item.html?item=249&mid=101197043325464>&nbsp;</a><a id=sj href=item.html?item=249&mid=101197043325464>Not worth the trouble.</a> <a id=fs8 href=item.html?item=249&mid=101197043325464#post><img src=http://everquest.allakhazam.com/static/reply.gif border=0 alt="Reply..." height=16 width=16></a>
	     <br clear=all><small>Posted @ Fri, Jan 25th 10:55 AM 2002</small></td></tr>
	     <tr><td valign=top id=fs8 class=mform><span id=notbold>By:</span> <a href=poster.html?user=31407><span id=Sage>zhmoozo</span></a><br><b><span id=Sage>Sage</span></b><br><span id=notbold>198 posts<br><span id=notbold>Score</span>: Good [3.53]</td><td valign=top class=mform width=100%><p>Fooey.<br><br>Given the extreme rarity of the two mobs needed to complete the quest that produces this item, I'd say a person was better off just buying a well-balanced scimitar from Shady in East Commons, a Coldain velium scimitar in Thurgadin or even a mob-dropped velium scimitar from another player depending on their budget.<br><br>Face it, by the time a druid is high enough to do the quest, s/he won't be doing much melee anymore anyway.&nbsp;&nbsp;You'll be using it mainly to finish things off =after= they have gone into flee mode so you don't need to waste any mana on another nuke.  Face it, druids at this level have lousy AC, and they don't generally do very well in toe-to-toe melee battles with the mobs they would be hunting for XP.  That's a tactic they need to learn to give up as they pass through their teens.<br><br>As a druid, rather than doing this quest, I'd say that you'd be better off investing your time doing other things, even if you do get lucky enough to bump into both Groi and Tiny the Timbur.  I've spent a huge amount of time hunting in both SK and NK and I've only seen Groi once, and I've never, ever seen Tiny.<br><br>As evidence of the fact that these mobs are rare, try to find info on them online.  There isn't much out there, guys.  And looking for price quotes on this scimitar is a joke.  As I write this there hasn't been one, single price quote entered here for it, and this item has been in game for nearly 3 years!  That suggests that it is very VERY rare that anybody gets one of these.<br><br>And as others here have already pointed out, the pack alone is probably worth more than the scimitar.<br><br>:)<br><br></p>&nbsp;<br>Shmoozo<br></td></td></tr>
